        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 2026</p>

        <p>This notice is provided pursuant to EU Regulation 2016/679 (GDPR) and describes how the personal data of users who browse the website <strong>buildhub.it</strong> and use our services is processed.</p>

        <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
        <p>The Data Controller is <strong>Build Hub</strong>, based in Catania (CT), Italy.<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:buildhubitalia@gmail.com">buildhubitalia@gmail.com</a></p>

        <h2>2. Types of data collected</h2>
        <p>Through our website we exclusively collect the data that the user voluntarily chooses to provide via:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The <strong>contact form</strong> on the Contact page: full name, email address, phone number, services of interest and message content.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not collect browsing data through profiling cookies or tracking tools. We use only <strong>technical cookies</strong> essential for the functioning of the website. For more information please refer to the <a href="cookie.html">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>

        <h2>3. Purposes of processing</h2>
        <p>The personal data provided voluntarily by the user is processed for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to <strong>information and consultation requests</strong> sent via the contact form.</li>
          <li>To fulfil any <strong>pre-contractual, contractual and tax obligations</strong> arising from the relationship established with the user.</li>
          <li>To send service communications strictly related to the user's request.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Legal basis</h2>
        <p>The processing is based on the <strong>explicit consent</strong> of the data subject (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR), expressed by voluntarily submitting their data via the contact form and accepting this privacy notice. For contractual purposes, the legal basis is the performance of pre-contractual and contractual measures (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR).</p>

        <h2>5. Methods and duration of processing</h2>
        <p>Data is processed using electronic and paper-based tools, adopting adequate technical and organisational security measures to ensure the confidentiality and integrity of the data. Data is retained for the time strictly necessary to respond to the user's request and, in any case, for a period not exceeding <strong>24 months</strong> from the last interaction, unless legal obligations require longer retention.</p>

        <h2>6. Communication and transfer of data</h2>
        <p>Personal data is not transferred to third parties for commercial purposes. It may be communicated to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Professionals and collaborators</strong> of Build Hub, where necessary to handle the user's request.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical service providers</strong> (hosting, site maintenance) appointed as Data Processors pursuant to Art. 28 GDPR.</li>
          <li><strong>Public authorities</strong>, exclusively in cases provided for by law.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Data is not transferred outside the European Economic Area.</p>

        <h2>7. Rights of the data subject</h2>
        <p>Pursuant to Articles 15-22 of the GDPR, the user has the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Obtain <strong>confirmation</strong> of the existence of personal data concerning them and its communication in an intelligible form (right of access).</li>
          <li>Obtain the <strong>rectification</strong>, <strong>integration</strong> or <strong>erasure</strong> of data.</li>
          <li>Obtain the <strong>restriction</strong> of processing.</li>
          <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing on legitimate grounds.</li>
          <li>Receive data in a structured format (<strong>portability</strong>).</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time, without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent given before its withdrawal.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. How to exercise rights</h2>
        <p>The user may exercise their rights at any time by writing to <a href="mailto:buildhubitalia@gmail.com">buildhubitalia@gmail.com</a>. Requests will be processed within 30 days. The user also has the right to lodge a complaint with the Italian Data Protection Authority (<a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.garanteprivacy.it</a>).</p>

        <h2>9. Changes to this notice</h2>
        <p>This notice may be subject to changes over time. Users are invited to periodically review this page. The date of the last update is indicated at the top of the document.</p>

